# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the version is
#   managed by the developer. For an app, you might want to commit them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you choose to not commit it:
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally committed, but can be excluded if desired.
